{"_id":"000ebdYiQnk7rwbt","name":"Ruinous Power","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/surrounded-eye.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You obtain power, but at what cost? The eyes of your Daemon are fixated on you, judging you – eager to reward, or to punish.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You immediately gain a Disorder. In addition, select one of your Covenant's Aspects and replace your Order Alignment with it. Instead of gaining Fate Points, you may opt to gain a Daemonic Gift. Aspects and Daemonic Gifts are found in Chapter 6: Liber Umbrarum. When you generate face ‘6’ with Chaos Dice, you invoke a Chaos Manifestation. Furthermore, you must add 1 additional Chaos Die when Channeling Power. Finally, you must eat three meals a day or else suffer from Starvation (as outlined under Starvation from the Hazards & Healing chapter in ZWEIHÄNDER)."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"09HP1kCV6Dkmw6Ad","name":"When the Dealin’s Done","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/morbid-humour.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Living forever is boring and the Gambler will burn out before they fade away. And when you play the devil’s game, you eventually get the devil’s reward.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you use a Fortune Point for Luck of the Draw, you move one step down the Peril Condition Track negatively."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"0HRVtKE9hJOQI9DG","name":"Alter Ego","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/bat-mask.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The powers-above will not cast their favor upon you, until you don the mask of a Vigilante.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When in places where you may be recognized as anyone other than your moniker, you cannot use Fate Points."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"0KdUmM1H6Fln7q3W","name":"Melancholic Temperament","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"","notes":"","value":"You are prone to fits of fatigue, and oftentimes suffer from phantom pains in your muscles. In fact, it's hard to rouse you from war-weariness without using twice the normal medication required to lift your spirits."},"effect":{"value":""},"effects":"Whenever you use Smelling Salts, you must use two instead of one. Using an additional dose of Smelling Salts in this instance has no negative effects."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"1BE1hUIpSwet1fET","name":"Nemesis","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"","notes":"","value":"You have an implacable enemy that harries you at every opportunity. They may be a political rival who sabotages your ambitions or a foe who is destined to kill you. Perhaps your Nemesis may yet be unnamed, revealed at a much later date."},"effect":{"value":""},"effects":"When confronted by your Nemesis, you cannot sacrifice Fate or Fortune Points, as their presence confounds you. Your Nemesis is determined by the GM, who will likely take your ideas about your Character’s history or past rivals into consideration."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"1eZcfLBV4tEZ0eaG","name":"Mutagenic Transformation","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/fire-bottle.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"After swallowing a host of mutagenic compounds, a Hexer is born. However, they become sterile as a result of their mutations.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You gain the Eunuch Drawback upon entering this Profession. In addition, you are also considered both a Humanoid and Mutant for purposes of being affected by Magick, Toxins and the like."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"2BD9F6Ki8zTVPhXH","name":"Hard of Hearing","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/horn-internal.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The high-pitch sounds of war machines operating and bombastic explosions of gunpowder have left you partially deaf. Or, maybe you are just dense, and care little to listen to others as the power of a god rests in your very hands!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You cannot add Skill Ranks to Skill Tests that rely on hearing or speaking aloud."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"2jLdwVtjN3Y6in0H","name":"Eunuch","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"","notes":"","value":"You were castrated for one reason or another. Your gelding has deeply impacted you, a harrowing memory you find difficult to suppress. Perhaps you were a monk who became a eunuch after a spiritual awakening. Or, maybe you were gelded for acts of sexual indecency. Either way, you decide what led you to this end. The sting of being unable to have children weighs heavily upon you. Your bloodline has ended."},"effect":{"value":""},"effects":"You are immune to the charms and seduction by those who find you attractive, and unable to have children. However, being made victim to these same charms and seduction causes you to suffer 1 Corruption."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"2l5wEUEyl7dRWjBm","name":"Savagery","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Your martial spirit is not easily sated and you are large in both raw appetite, adventurous spirit and belligerent attitudes.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately change your Order Alignment to Ferocity and your Chaos Alignment to Hatred."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"2nlqGrttW6LcFYBB","name":"Code of Honor","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/classical-knowledge.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Grail Knights hold themselves to a higher standard in comparison with other knights, and indeed, the rest of civilization. They thoroughly despise the use of bows, pistols and the like, seeing them as the weapons of cowards and unskilled warriors. Nor will they attack an enemy unseen.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You cannot use ranged weapons whatsoever, nor attack during a Surprise Turn or from ambush."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"3Tm5w0gKdMocZL3l","name":"Sour Stomach","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You have pains in your stomach that make it difficult to keep down ‘rich’ food. This also means other kinds of substances can have a poor effect on your health, and keep you confined to the water closet.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"After taking a dose of Laudanum, a Delirient or consuming a substance the GM sees as being hard on your stomach, you cannot recover to Unhindered on the Peril Condition Track (only to Imperiled) for the next 24-hours."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"40bRkbVS8QfsGl7P","name":"Sea-Borne Fear","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/kraken-tentacle.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Reaver does not trust the seas or the ocean, for they nor their horse can drink from it.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you cross a body of salt water (out of sight of land), you are made victim to Fear."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"5YB4PaPVJjzSaasg","name":"Split Face","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Whether you took the haft of an axe to the face, your nose was broken in a fight or were born with a deformity, you have a poor sense of smell.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You must flip the results to fail all Skill Tests which rely on smell and taste."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"615qjkafZPKI4eCX","name":"Grey Temperament","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Property, wealth and largesse is of little use to the Illusionist. To them, they regard the aesthetics of the world around them as their bounty, carrying only what is necessary on them to survive.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You cannot accumulate property, except for what you may be able to carry upon yourself. Violation of this sacred tenet causes your Magick to automatically fail otherwise."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"690JtyKbpVJuJdHX","name":"Weak Lungs","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You have suffered a terrible injury at some point, making it difficult to breath. You may have fallen on a fencepost as a youth and grown up with the use of only one lung. Perhaps you were stabbed by a vicious rival and now exhibit an audible wheezing.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you suffer physical Peril, move one additional step down the Peril Condition Track negatively while suffering 1 Corruption."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"6mf5OgbHt3uyMAen","name":"Damned","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Unfortunately, the power you wield is highly destructive – not only to others, but to your very soul.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You immediately gain a Malignancy. Any time you gain a Disorder, you gain a Malignancy as\n  well (as outlined under Malignancies from the Game Mastery chapter in ZWEIHÄNDER)."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"6nIPbE3DZorxYjgw","name":"Crop Ear","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"","notes":"","value":"An unfortunate accident, or a result of birth or disease has left you partially deaf. You are barely able to hear and must rely on your other senses to process the world around you. Speech is difficult and you're often misunderstood or even ridiculed as you converse with others."},"effect":{"value":""},"effects":"You must flip the results to fail all Skill Tests that rely on hearing."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"6rFrlF4UVIJRBk70","name":"Damned","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Unfortunately, the power you wield is highly destructive – not only to others, but to your very soul.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Any time you gain a Disorder, you gain a Malignancy as well."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"7vbLaAm6qUGb1kpB","name":"Black Hat","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Every protagonist of the story has a rival; an implacable villain that haunts their every turn. You are no different, and this heel will follow you to the ends of the earth to see you humiliated or killed.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You gain the Nemesis Drawback upon entering this Profession. If you already have a Nemesis, you gain another."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"800XO1nklFvzWAja","name":"Diabolical Mark","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You have denied the gods outright and they have now denied you in return. It doesn’t necessarily mean that your prayers go unanswered. In fact, they’re still granted, but by new masters. For your subservience, you are branded with a mark, sealing your obedience to the Abyssal Princes of the endless pit.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You no longer suffer from Divine Punishment, but instead invoke Chaos Manifestations as if you were using Arcane Magick. In addition, you must always Channel Power when casting Magick, costing 0 AP to do so in combat. When you Critically Fail an Incantation Test to cast Magick, your skin is branded with a permanent ‘devil’s mark’. For each mark, you automatically gain one Chaos Rank."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"883mxHUj2vkGdijS","name":"Death Has Come to Town","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/cloaked-figure-on-horseback.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"<p>When a Plague Doktor comes calling, the people scatter. They hold an inalienable fear of their grim practice, as their beaked masks and black garb are oftentimes conflated with images of the Custodian himself. As such, you have found it difficult to keep close friends, as most perish in your company as you are undeniably a plague carrier.</p>","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"<p>When you fail Fellowship-based Skill Tests, they are treated as if they were Critical Failures instead.</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"kxLIOLOpmFRWf8Ew":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.7LVHFn69B7mwNrFU"}}}
{"_id":"8hVwb0ETfks5QIuq","name":"Gospel of Desolation","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The world is going to end – there is no doubt in your mind. You treat every battle as if it would be your last. And, it must be a glorious end.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You immediately gain a Disorder. In addition, you can never wear armor as it violates your tenets. Should you don armor, you do not gain the benefits of any Professional Trait – Fanatic or otherwise – that you possess."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"8mavFk680Ix6MueH","name":"Deal with the Devil","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Your family is cursed, having struck a Faustian bargain with a dark power. Written in blood, this contract guaranteed that your ancestors had to give up a part of their soul. Now, this deal falls to you and your offspring.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You begin gameplay with one permanent Chaos Rank."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"92ndBXiHV0a7boJq","name":"Green Temperament","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Elementalists must maintain harmony with nature in order to draw from the Æthereal Veil. Should they disrupt the forces of order and tip the balance towards disorder, it brings about an internal turmoil which cannot easily be ignored, outside of intense meditation and reflection.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"If you are suffering from 6 or more Corruption, you cannot cast Magick."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"94JAFIzomT2aZnU8","name":"Choleric Temperament","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/enrage.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"<p>You have a tendency of one-upmanship, are rather prickly and frankly, bossy. When things don&rsquo;t go your way in a fight, you grow irritated, which only further pushes you towards embracing your Chaos Alignment.</p>","notes":"","value":"You have a tendency of one-upmanship, are rather prickly and frankly, bossy. When things don't go your way in a fight, you grow irritated, which only further pushes you towards embracing your Chaos Alignment."},"effect":{"value":"<p>Whenever you roll Chaos Dice to determine if you Injure a foe and fail to do so, move one step down the Peril Condition Track negatively while suffering 1 Corruption.</p>"},"effects":"Whenever you roll Chaos Dice to determine if you Injure a foe and fail to do so, move one step down the Peril Condition Track negatively while suffering 1 Corruption."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"97ZUqf20FOmTdeKz","name":"Cursed","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"","notes":"","value":"A terrible twist of fate or dark Magick has cast a hex over you. Your curse may have originated from an act of cruelty served upon the innocent, born from mortal sin; a dreadful stigma that has afflictedyourfamilyoraterribleMagickthat'sbeencastuponyou. Curses of this magnitude oftentimes plague individuals until their death. Only a major sacrifice can potentially lift the curse and the cost is likely greater than you can levy. It may be that your Order or Chaos Alignment is somehow tied to the curse."},"effect":{"value":""},"effects":"Whenever you intend to sacrifice a Fortune Point, roll a 1D6 Chaos Die. If the result is a face '6', you must use two Fortune Points instead of one."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"A0RVzMyQDap6Wq2D","name":"Debt-ridden","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You have spent and spent and spent, borrowing far too much money without the possibility of return to your creditors. You may have even been committed to a debtor’s prison. This carries a social stigma, leaving a black stain upon your shield of reputation and conscience. As such, you find it exceedingly difficult – if not impossible – to come to any sort of middle ground with others given your history.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You must flip the results to fail all Skill Tests that rely on your ability to barter, bargain or strike monetary deals in your favor."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"AG7fCX4RXKvOoajE","name":"Lure of Power","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/temptation.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The wellspring of Magickal power is immeasurable. It woefully draws its practitioners deeper and deeper into its embrace, corrupting both the soul and the world around them.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you generate face '6' with Chaos Dice, you invoke a Chaos Manifestation."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"AVYtNGoKTvfc1ftF","name":"Achilles Heel","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Despite your (mostly) unerring martial attitudes, you become overwhelmed when facing three or more combatants at once.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When attackers outnumber you 3:1 or more in an Engagement, they add a 1D6 Fury Die to Total Damage results made with melee weapons against you. This means you can never take advantage of the Impenetrable Wall Talent."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Av8txBAacRzcdXWx","name":"The World is Mine","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"With an air of affluence and confidence, Merchant Lords have few perceived weaknesses, save for their indulgences in coin, food and flesh.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately change your Order Alignment to Sophistication and your Chaos Alignment to Indulgence."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"B7rtNBBpyAAtmHTU","name":"The Learner’s Commandments","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/wax-tablet.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Learner makes specific demands from His priesthood. Truthsayers should always seek to speak the truth under all circumstances and abide by the law. They must volunteer to arbitrate disputes, and must lean on reason before picking up the sword.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you would normally invoke a Chaos Manifestation, you instead provoke Punishments of the Learner. In addition, you are bound by the commandments of your god. You must seek atonement if you violate these commandments."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"CJq9F7h5Q64Z9bbY","name":"Assassin’s Creed","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"One must have a callous indifference towards the sanctity of life to become an Assassin. This career tends to draw the bloodthirsty and insane to its ranks. Assassins who are consumed by the act of killing are utterly corrupted, while others who maintain proper decorum will remain untainted by their grisly work.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you take an innocent life unprovoked, you automatically gain 1 permanent Chaos Rank."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Cf1R7mSlDEAQPW7t","name":"Cruel Tutelage","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/magic-palm.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"As Cultists are wholly self-taught in the ways of Magick, the practice of their spells is messy and chaotic. Fortunate for Abyssal Princes sensitive to this errant way of thinking, Cultists and their ilk make easy prey, leading them down a path towards the blackest and most soul-corrupting of Magicks.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you generate face ‘1’ or ‘6’ with Chaos Dice, you invoke a Chaos Manifestation."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"E1WR1vI6HRD9M41F","name":"Bad Ticker","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You suffer from a debilitating sickness, which makes your blood stir slowly. It is slowly eating away at your precious humanity bit-by-bit, and inevitably will lead to your doom.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you fail to Resist against Stress, Fear or Terror, you gain 3 additional Corruption."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EilnrNsVS45Jgr3M","name":"Veteran's Leg","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"With a characteristic shuffling, you draw your lame leg behind you. Attached at the knee cap with a Barber Surgeon’s contraption, the cheap prosthesis grants you the ability to walk (albeit at a slow, deliberate pace).","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You must reduce your Movement by 3 and cannot Run."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Er2XZVV7RiqasaB3","name":"Death Wish","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Unfortunately, the path of the Slayer is a difficult one that only the truly insane would possibly follow.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"In order to follow the Slayer’s Path, you can never wear armor as it violates this tenet. Should you don armor, you do not gain the benefits of any Professional Trait – Slayer or otherwise – that you possess."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"F2m1N1tZOtS05mPM","name":"Lily-Livered","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/butterfly.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You get butterflies in your stomach in the most innocuous of situations. It cannot be helped, and when forced into strange and otherworldly situations, your legs tremble and you have a hard time concentrating.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you fail to Resist Stress, Fear or Terror, you temporarily reduce your Initiative and Movement by -3 (to a minimum of 1). This lasts until you get a good night's rest."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"FpuzGl88vbbG2a1C","name":"Veteran's Hand","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Whether it was lopped off at the hands of a vicious mercenary or somehow torn asunder in the complex cogs of a war machine, you lost use of your hand long ago. In its place is an iron prosthesis, clumsy to attach and difficult to use. A webbing of leather straps adorns your arm, from wrist to elbow.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You cannot hold weapons which are two-handed and must flip the results to fail any Skill Test requiring use of both hands."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"FzSxi7O7D64G82j1","name":"Grumbler","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Being a remnant of the old guard, you can’t help but struggle adjusting to new things. It is your duty to remind these youngbloods that sometimes the old ways are the best ways.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately change your Order Alignment to Wisdom and your Chaos Alignment to Rancor. In addition, you must spend an additional 50 Reward Points to buy Skill Ranks."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"GSSurkTUOwpZzzrG","name":"Abstain From Violence","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/truce.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You have given yourself to the god’s mercy, taking no part in the selfish passions nor acts of violence. You are a pacifist at heart and it brings you great sorrow when you do hurt another – even if they would intend to kill you.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Should you intentionally bring harm upon a creature classified as a Humanoid (including player Ancestries), you are unable to call upon your White Witchery abilities for three days."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Ho8V4n0MJ5qSQ2NK","name":"Strictures of the Order","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Chevaliers have a strong sense of commitment to their order. To\n  turn away from their post or to abandon their ideal is almost\n  unheard of.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately change your Order Alignment to Duty and your Chaos Alignment to Fatalism."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"I0eE6lCigDiLcJIV","name":"Political Rivalry","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"In the course of your career, you’ve earned a powerful political enemy. Both they and their followers have goals opposed to yours and will defame, embarrass and shame to achieve them. They may even be willing to kill you!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You gain the Nemesis Drawback upon entering this Profession. If you already have a Nemesis, you gain another."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"IHMqtUGaDG6T5bYD","name":"Avowed","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Although Friars are not monastic, they have taken a sacred vow of poverty, ministry and evangelizing. Should you stray from the path, you are wracked with extreme guilt, a sin which requires tithe or self-flagellation to correct.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You cannot accumulate property, except for what you may be able to carry upon yourself. Violation of this sacred tenet means you cannot add Skill Ranks to Skill Tests, until you unburden yourself by donating the excess to your religious order and causing yourself enough harm to move three steps down the Peril Condition Track negatively."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ITdiaGklrk5epo54","name":"Runic Instability","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Your Runic enhancements are unstable, and threaten to explode with Ætheric might. Your Runes cannot be inscribed upon living things – unfortunate for those who wished to raise a litter of exploding kittens!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever an object you have inscribed a Rune upon is broken, Ruined! or Wrecked!, it explodes, destroying the object. Those caught in a Burst Template area of effect must succeed at a (Challenging -10%) Coordination Test or suffer 3D10+3 Damage from fire."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"IhAWLMMU2FtJTWp4","name":"Monstrous Weakness","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/achilles-heel.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Like an ancient creature of the world, you are particularly susceptible to certain metals and Magicks. Eventually, you will become victim to it in ways that are worse than death, dragged onto all fours as the animal you worship.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you are struck by weapons wrought from Cold Iron or Mithril and those which have been imbued with Magick, you suffer an additional 3 Damage. In addition, whenever you gain 1 permanent Chaos Rank, a Disorder or Malignancy, you also permanently suffer a -1 penalty to Encumbrance. Should your Encumbrance permanently reach zero, you are immediately Slain!, turned entirely into the spirit you worship."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"In4s1ArMmuOYsIfa","name":"Wallow In Misery","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Rune Thane devotes everything to their work; they are not just a fair-weather researcher, but a scholar and a champion for the runic arts. Thus, when they fail at their job, they become cloistered and sour for they take the failure particularly hard.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"After a Rune Thane fails the empowerment cycle, they must flip the results to fail all Incantation Tests for one hour if having failed an Apprentice Rune, one day if having failed a Journeyman Rune or one week if having failed a Master Rune. In addition, they cannot attempt to inscribe new Runes during this time."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"IrfGFLuZT9Ht0FIj","name":"For the Glory!","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Blitzballers have a reputation to uphold. That reputation is oftentimes foisted upon others by constantly roaring and pumping their fist from the thrill of violence, but such is the life of these dunderheads.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You must always leave one hand free. This means you cannot wield 2 one-handed weapons, a two-handed weapon or a weapon with shield. Otherwise, you cannot use any of your Traits or Talents conferred by this Profession."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"J4MjdrHLvIz1Yb5w","name":"Black Temperament","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Unfortunately, the power you wield is highly destructive – not only to others, but also upon your very soul. Bit by bit, your spirit is consumed by the dark sorcery you wield. You begin to develop odd affectations and side effects from using the destructive powers of the blackest Ætheric Winds.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you Critically Fail an Incantation Test to cast Magick, you gain a Malignancy."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"JCz5U9P6rvb8amF4","name":"Branded","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/hades-symbol.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are one of the disenfranchised of society; the bonded, a serf, slave or thrall. You are looked upon poorly by most of society, treated with some manner of contempt or apprehension, if acknowledged at all. Most of those Branded take great pains to hide the shame of their past. Perhaps you were even the bastard born progeny of an unknown father! It is up to you to decide why you were branded.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you interact with those who know you’re Branded and hold you in contempt due to it, you cannot succeed at Fellowship-based Skill Tests to interact with them."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"JQXjT2ZAPXyXvLSn","name":"Enjoy the Silence","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/mute.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Badlanders enjoy the solitude of the wilderness more than others. They treat others with extreme discrimination, seeing their presence as more a distraction than a boon.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You never Critically Succeed at Fellowship-based Skill Tests, even if you roll a Match. In addition, you cannot take advantage of Talents, Traits, Magick or Fortune Points to modify any Fellowship-based Skill Test."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"K3yZCW81Li0LtGQ8","name":"Washed Up","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Leaving behind the life they once lived, the Rake is now forced to rub elbows with the friends they’ve got, as opposed to the ones they had.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you enter this Profession, immediately change your Social Class to Lowborn."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"K9Rskdir34lAKyXI","name":"The God-Emperor’s Commandments","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/wax-tablet.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The God-Emperor makes specific demands from His priesthood. Some of these include obeying your king. Others may be rooting out the Mutant incursion. You must befriend dwarves, and do your best to ally with them. Most of these edicts require you to sacrifice personal liberty so that justice is fulfilled for all.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you would normally invoke a Chaos Manifestation, you instead provoke Punishments of the GodEmperor. In addition, you are bound by the commandments of your god. You must seek atonement if you violate these commandments."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"KDcjMf2dH4BmMgF0","name":"Salt of the Earth","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Despicable wretch! Lowly worm! Kneel before your betters, and polish my boots while you’re at it!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you enter this Profession, immediately change your Social Class to Lowborn."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"MMfE4vXPDsEqthp8","name":"High-Handed","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"War Generals are oftentimes more concerned with the point of the spear, not the heavy lifting required to get soldiers and supplies to the front.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"For every step you move down the Peril Condition Track negatively, reduce your Initiative and Movement in kind. As an example, if you are suffering from Imperiled, you would reduce your Initiative and Movement by a -1 penalty."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"MQyymDZxL7F9uerP","name":"Quackery","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The quality of your ‘remedies’ is questionable, at best.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"After a person imbibes one of your alchemical concoctions and goes to sleep, roll a 1D6 Chaos Die. On a result of face ‘1-5’ nothing happens. On a result of face ‘6’, the imbiber suffers 2D10+2 physical Peril."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Ma1ed8SzkViusumF","name":"Noblesse Oblige","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Nobility extends beyond mere entitlements and a Mootwarden who claims such status must fulfill their obligation.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately change your Order Alignment to Duty and your Chaos Alignment to Fatalism."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"NT8jra8lDl6kRpop","name":"The Custodian’s Commandments","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/wax-tablet.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Custodian makes specific demands from Her priesthood. They must remain steady foes to the befouled Crouching One, taking all means to bring their cult to an end. They must defend places where the dead are buried and cannot disturb those who have been chosen by the Custodian to enter Her sacred realms. But of all Her strictures, none is more demanding than that which states all necromancers and those who’d raise the dead unnaturally must be hunted down.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you would normally invoke a Chaos Manifestation, you instead provoke Punishments of the Custodian. In addition, you are bound by the commandments of your god, as outlined in Chapter 10: Grimoire. You must seek atonement if you violate these commandments."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"OdGBkmSHNZCrNEWC","name":"Veteran's Boot","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Perhaps lost during an unfortunate carriage\n  accident, during an intense battle, or in the jaws of a\n  rabid animal, you are missing a foot. In its place is a wooden boot, which you must strap onto your leg to stand up straight. It makes a characteristic ‘CLUD’ sound as you walk, which has earned you a number of embarrassing nicknames.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You cannot Charge, Maneuver or Run with Movement Actions without spending an additional Action Point."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"P3oVI82WAx7FmC6X","name":"Scarred Psyche","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Unfortunately, your cynicism is difficult to hide, the scars upon your psyche visible to all. This carries through both in your personal and professional life, triggering during instances of intense stress or pain. This sickness may send you into a blinding rage or cause you to cower in the corner like a squalling babe.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you fail Willpower-based Skill Tests, they are treated as if they were Critical Failures instead."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"PZcE7yjfy1LNXEFS","name":"Hireling's Dilemma","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Henchmen often go unrecognized for their sacrifices and rarely win accolades for their daring-do.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Treat a result of 1% on percentile dice as a Critical Failure, no matter whether you would have succeeded or Critically Succeeded the Skill Test."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"SjomKFjTKvb8XEw4","name":"Master & Servant","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Chamberlains have a strong sense of commitment to their sovereign. To turn away from their post or to abandon their ideal is almost unheard of.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately change your Order Alignment to Duty and your Chaos Alignment to Fatalism."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"TnX7rbBH4C8HoL9R","name":"Intellectual Rigor","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Scholars are slavishly devoted to the truth. To speak an untruth or stretch the truth thin is not only grossly negligent towards their studies, but is a mark upon their shield of reputation and stake in the scientific community.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Any time you tell a lie, cheat or spread a falsehood, you gain 3 Corruption."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"U27l0zIPrxZcxjzb","name":"You Can’t Handle the Truth!","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"It takes a certain kind of personality to become a Military Officer. One must be highly disciplined, be able to take orders and carry out even the most unusual or morally questionable acts without question.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately change your Order Alignment to Ferocity and your Chaos Alignment to Hatred."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"UVWaCzwXCbUzgP14","name":"The Leviathan’s Commandments","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/wax-tablet.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Leviathan makes specific demands from Her priesthood. Whistling aboard a ship is considered unlucky, as is leaving any port with a lad aboard named Jonah. Meat of animals born on the land cannot be eaten. For the most part, these demands are traditional sailor’s superstitions only exacerbated by their cult tenfold and heavily ritualized.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you would normally invoke a Chaos Manifestation, you instead provoke Punishments of the Leviathan. In addition, you are bound by the commandments of your god, as outlined in Chapter 10: Grimoire. You must seek atonement if you violate these commandments."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"UcVKfr1JZV0akhO6","name":"Persecution Complex","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Everyone – literally, everyone – is out to get you. There is no doubt in your mind that others may be following you, are trying to trick you or are ridiculing you behind your back.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You cannot rest to recover from Peril in urban environments, unless you take a dose of laudanum before resting."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Um3sf0cs7igypQlN","name":"Ever-faithful","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Pledged Guard, no matter their master, maintains the strictest sense of loyalty. While they may serve many lords and ladies over time, a Pledged Guard has an unerring sense of duty to only one charge at a time, which sometimes leads them down the path to destruction.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately change your Order Alignment to Duty and your Chaos Alignment to Fatalism."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Um5cUvRl3sSiSL9M","name":"Forger's Fourrée","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Being a master counterfeiter has its perks and disadvantages. Despite the sheer quality of your fraudulent work, trafficking it into the local economy makes you extremely nervous. Thus, you often work through a Fence.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever attempting to buy, sell or trade forged materials or use counterfeited coins, you cannot use Fortune Points to modify your Skill Test results."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"VKcK3Tzf8kAigtJF","name":"Purple Temperament","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Rumors persist that Funerary Mages are nothing more than Necromancers in disguise, seeking both paths to find the truth to unlife. Given this unsavory (and unfair) reputation, it is no wonder that Funerary Mages are curt, grim and detached from the rest of the world. They do not make friends easily, nor are their words ever seen as friendly given their grave nature.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You never Critically Succeed at Fellowship-based Skill Tests, even if you roll a Match. In addition, you cannot take advantage of Talents, Traits, Magick or Fortune Points to modify any Fellowship-based Skill Test."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"WYS5DdMPxHRpkWoM","name":"Watch your Back","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Outlaw Chief is always mindful of ‘beta knaves’ trying to usurp the top dog.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you fail Resolve Tests, you suffer from Stress."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Wl1bTXy0u7ICmB99","name":"Dead Or Alive","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Should you waiver or fail in your duty, you will carry the weight of the Blood Oath until it sees its end... or yours.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you enact a Blood Oath, you are considered to be under the effects of Vow of Fealty (as outlined under Generalist Magick from the Grimoire\n    chapter in ZWEIHÄNDER)."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"WoXVcGFyxL6wK7uJ","name":"Red Temperament","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/fire-silhouette.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Pyromancers are famously mercurial, possessing quick tempers and heated emotions. Woe be to others should they stand in your way, for they cannot assuage your anger!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you suffer Damage, you must immediately succeed at a Resolve Test or else suffer from Stress."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"XP2tgnizCdQJwgiJ","name":"Sanguine Temperament","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are rather outgoing, but also jittery and have a hard time sitting still. You may suffer from ‘jimmy leg’, and are unable to keep a steady hand in the thick of battle, unless concentrating.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You cannot Load or Take Aim without spending an additional Action Point. In addition, whenever you use the Special Action of Wait, you lose 1 Action Point."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Xu2B23HG3vQoskvN","name":"Nirvana","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/enlightenment.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Bladedancers value individualism over traditionalism. The struggle they face is having to shed their humanity to find enlightenment. Their ultimate goal: to enter a final, blessed state marked by the absence of suffering and desire.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately change your Order Alignment to Enlightenment and your Chaos Alignment to Detachment."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Y3LeEbkpzUuO0Oun","name":"Vow of 'Nonviolence'","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Most find it deeply ironic that Apostles take upon bludgeoning instruments to convert others to their faith. To an Apostle, bloodshed is ‘at least’ mitigated in this fashion, as their martial instrument of conversion serves as a grim reminder to not denigrate the faith.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can only use weapons that are of the Brawling or Crushing types. Otherwise, you cannot use any of your Traits or Talents conferred by this Profession."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Y5AOKYbxWOBKTX5x","name":"Callous Attitudes","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Slavers who relish in subjugating others often take to this trade. Each vicious act of the Chattel Slaver eats away at their precious humanity bit by bit.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you suffer Corruption, increase the number you gain by one. This means that if you suffer 3 Corruption, you gain 4 instead."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"YkJ1g1ZnFObmIGgd","name":"Dunderhead","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are socially awkward and don’t get along well with others. You often stammer, lose focus and find it hard to compel others to listen to you. As such, you are perceived as being socially inept at times, or haughty without reason. You may even have a brain trauma! You decide.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you suffer mental Peril, move one additional step down the Peril Condition Track negatively while suffering 1 Corruption."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"YloBtzjHCHs6nJlN","name":"Skin Deep","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"People have a hard time looking past your beauty, and generally ignore the deeper aspects of your personality and skills. As such, you must work twice as hard to prove yourself","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You cannot Assist other Characters unless you have at least two Skill Ranks in the Skill you are Assisting."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ZIFOYVWP1OVVKTCZ","name":"Religious Zealotry","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Inquisitors are a dogged folk, zealous to the point of posing danger to themselves and their friends around them.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately change your Order Alignment to Zeal and your Chaos Alignment to Fanaticism."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ZTq77A481RHMQeiL","name":"The Martyr’s Commandments","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/wax-tablet.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Revered Mothers should always offer to heal the sick and give their services without promise of payment in return. Most have never even taken another life, even to defend the weak. However, they remain fervent in their crusade against chaos and are given reprieve from some strictures to defend others against those pained by Abyssal possession or those born of chaos made flesh.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you would normally invoke a Chaos Manifestation, you instead provoke Punishments of the Martyr. In addition, you are bound by the commandments of your god. You must seek atonement if you violate these commandments."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"azdWb8ervuUtPxgp","name":"Icarus Complex","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/icarus.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Unsurprisingly, Natural Philosophers are overly-ambitious, thus blind to any faults or dangers that may be found in their studies. Many have fallen victim to their own insane machineries – recall the story of Daedalus’ folly.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Any time you or someone else Critically Fails at an attempt to use a fantastic machine or Golem you have crafted or it is Ruined!, Slain! or Wrecked!, roll a 1D6 Chaos Die. On a result of face ‘1-5’, it fails to work, requiring a week to clean and repair. On a result of face ‘6’, it explodes, effectively destroyed. Those caught in a Burst Template area of effect must succeed at a (Challenging -10%) Coordination Test or suffer 3D10+3 Damage from fire."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"bWf9b8rezzH4FRm1","name":"Wanderlust","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Nomad dislikes being tied down to one place permanently. A vagabond’s life is what best suits them.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Any time you are in an urban environment, you can never be restored to Unhindered on the Peril Condition Track, only to Imperiled."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"bkWeWggJRyaaiNKm","name":"Cramp My Style","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/leather-boot.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The art of fencing demands some particular joie de vivre; an exuberance of quality in flourish and style. As such, you refute the use of all armaments which do not fit into this worldview.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can only ever wear quilted armor to augment your Damage Threshold. Otherwise, you cannot use any of your Traits or Talents conferred by this Profession."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"brRo4ptVdhPWeLdG","name":"Bleeder","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Your blood doesn’t easily clot. This means you bruise like a peach when hurt, and spurt like a stuck pig whenever you are injured.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you are treated with the Heal Skill, a caregiver suffers an additional -20 Base Chance, unless they expend an additional bandage during treatment."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"cOaWDR6OvBPMf8tl","name":"Yellow Temperament","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Hermetics possess coldly logical minds and as hyper-rational individuals, they find it exceedingly difficult to entertain ideas which may not be theoretically sound or reasoned. As a consequence, they prefer to plan everything and invariably they find themselves grossly under-equipped to deal with factors that they cannot predict.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When your Chaos Ranks exceeds your Order Ranks, you must flip the results to fail all Fellowship-based Skill Tests. This lasts until your Order Ranks exceeds your Chaos Ranks."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"cV1sk8pSU7WPpbbz","name":"Quality of Mercy","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"War Dervishes are not intrinsically violent, but their training leads to the alignment of both body and weapon. Some use this for the sake of order, whereas some fight against the allure of chaos. Despite whether a justified killing or not, it leaves a stain upon the War Dervish’s soul.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you slay a creature that is of your own Ancestry, you suffer 3 Corruption."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"cc9a3UdCpfhBduwz","name":"Visor of Poor Visibility","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Ironclad as you are, you refuse to fight with the visor of your helmet up.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"While wearing armor with the Heavy Quality, you must flip the results to fail all Perception-based Skill Tests that rely on vision."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"cgng97RQYCUY3mf9","name":"Curse of Darkness","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Vampire Hunters are haunted by terrible dreams, and in them, they turn from hunter to hunted. Perhaps there is some truth within these nightmares, a precognition of the fate the Vampire Hunter is doomed to suffer.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Any time you suffer Damage or Peril from a Vampire, you suffer 3 Corruption."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"dM7cKhlzP48gmBc8","name":"The Crouching One’s Commandments","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/wax-tablet.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Crouching One makes specific demands from His priesthood. His Bloodmongers must spill the blood of animals in contrition and bleed themselves of foul humours often. Sometimes, they must carry out dangerous, ritualistic missions to assassinate specific people who displease the god. Rarer still they must indoctrinate their victim’s children into their sacred order, turning them into hired killers or worse.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you would normally invoke a Chaos Manifestation, you instead provoke Punishments of the Crouching One. In addition, you are bound by the commandments of your god, as outlined in Chapter 10: Grimoire. You must seek atonement if you violate these commandments."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"eLcR64F7lWbc695D","name":"Not Long for This World","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"It is said when the God-Emperor was a mortal man and obtained divine favor with the Winter King, He rose from his golden throne to begin a journey – and never returned, instead ascending into apotheosis. If a High Lector ever becomes so favored, they too wander away never to be seen again. Perhaps they embark on an endless quest or ascend into sainthood, but either way they fade into legend.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can never have more than 1 Fate Point at once. Should you ever possess 2 or more Fate Points, you must immediately sacrifice one."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ekxLtng24qW4r6Q5","name":"Guild Responsibilities","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Guildmaster’s life is one of constant expenditure – loans, bribes, banquets, the latest fashions for their significant other and so on – for the work they do is not enough to sustain their political power. It may be used for graft, further investiture and the training of new apprentices.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You must donate one out of nine coins you have to your guild."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"esmMSAMvCo78MtCS","name":"Red-Handed","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Whenever your acts of larceny have been discovered, you are unable to continue with your escapades until reaching safety.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you fail at an attempt to use Skulduggery or Stealth, you cannot use Fortune Points to change your results."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"f5kfPdZbPVpYSk9c","name":"Crestfallen","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/shattered-heart.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Hedge Knights are restricted by a code, a set of principles and guidelines they adhere to. When they bend or even break this code, they make themselves susceptible to chaos’ influence.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you suffer Corruption, increase the number of points you gain by one. This means that if you suffer 3 Corruption, you gain 4 instead."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"fCHfqQeJxIEo9jiC","name":"Blue Temperament","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"It is of no great surprise that Soothsayers are well-paid for their auguries. More so than their Astrologer counterparts, they can factually draw prognostications using their Magick to produce desired, real results. Abnormally wealthy, Soothsayers are ostentatious in their affectations, mannerisms, and style of dress.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You must always purchase the highest quality trappings available. This includes foodstuffs, supplies, weapons, armor, and other wares."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ftmWK646LfJ3iMz1","name":"Fugue State","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Once the strands of fate have been pulled apart, they cannot be woven together again so easily.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Once a person has used their Fate Point from your Weaver of Fate ability, you cannot walk for 1D10+1 days."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"g1YJTe6G1qdV8DGs","name":"Feeble-Mindedness","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Corruption affects everyone differently. For the Abbot, it does not result in the erosion of their spirit, but instead leads to frailty of the mind.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you would gain 10 Chaos Ranks, you do not gain a Disorder. Instead, reduce your Willpower by 9% each time you would normally gain a Disorder. Should your Willpower ever reach 0%, your Character must be retired."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"hfNp8Uszvt6FswFw","name":"Libera A Malo","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Exorcist walks on the razor’s edge, with one foot in the Abyss and the other in the Material Realm. This dangerous path can lead them to damnation in both body and spirit.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Any time you suffer Damage or Peril from a Restless Spirit, you suffer 3 Corruption."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"hy5Qa3RMTA4TeVf5","name":"Brown Temperament","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/bear-face.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Shamans have little patience for social conventions and are notoriously gruff, rude and grumpy. Shamans have no taste for the trappings of civility and make no means to hide this fact. They almost take pride in aggravating others, taking a sense of accomplishment with the people they scare or frighten due to their savage appearance.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When interacting directly with those of a Social Class other than Lowborn, you cannot succeed at Fellowship-based Skill Tests. In addition, you immediately move to the Lowborn Social Class once adopting this Profession."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"jKj5BYRICIQmkFF8","name":"Untrustworthy","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Despite having both the backing of the law and schooling, you are roundly mistrusted by others. Many see you as a blood-sucking, money-grubbing parasite of society. Inquisitors may even believe you may be, in fact, a blood-sucking vampire!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you fail any Fellowship-based Skill Test, you suffer 1 Corruption."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"jd7dLJrGmeWcjRNW","name":"Foolhardy","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Dungeoneers are generally stout-hearted people, possessed of the will to do good and right wrongs. However, their heroism sometimes borders on insanity, driven by the predilection to destroy all that is foul below. They’d make martyrs of themselves, if only to have their names spoken of in stories and song.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately change your Order Alignment to Heroism and your Chaos Alignment to Martyrdom."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"k6kbhHHsdNIVd9TB","name":"Devil-May-Care","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are a ‘stuntman’, taking wild chances and pushing your luck when no others would dare. As such, your reckless attitude makes you a liability.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You cannot use Fortune Points to change the results of any Skill Tests, save for Agility-based ones."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"kZv2auOOsRzxci2B","name":"Fortune & Glory","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Explorers are inexorably led, by their own egotism, to seek and recover artifacts, unearth lost knowledge and set forth their discoveries and theories about the world as the only truth. They’ll oftentimes forget that there are more powerful forces in the world that would keep them from revealing such knowledge, for curiosity kills the cat (and the Explorer).","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately change your Order Alignment to Adaptation and your Chaos Alignment to Mayhem."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"km9Dgf6FEGsaqcRO","name":"Notorious Moocher","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Living off the hard work of others, you manage to get by with but what’s in your pockets or what’s been given to you. Unfortunately, this casts an ill-light upon your reliability as you burn through your associates’ charity all too quickly.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When interacting with people who you know, you must flip the results to fail Fellowship-based Skill Tests."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ltGInmtf2UcPfJ22","name":"Public Enemy","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Your face and name are well-known. Very likely, there’s a reeve, bounty hunter or worse on your tail. As such, you are forced to live a life in the shadows, using trusted confidantes to carry out your tasks in public.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When in places where you may be recognized, you cannot use Fortune Points unless you make means to hide your true identity. The GM will likely ask you to make a Secret Test for Disguise when in public, only revealing the results at the most inopportune of times."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"lxXARkiSKPzk4wml","name":"And Justice for All","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Grand Master Dunklewasser von Artur once famously said, “... when I cross the river Lethe, my last conscious thoughts will be of the order, and the order, and the order.” Nothing is more sacred to a Grand Master than the order they serve, holding it above their own family and blood.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately change your Order Alignment to Pride and your Chaos Alignment to Arrogance."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"m1rqBK2hzPusk8hX","name":"Placebo Effect","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Unfortunately, your words sometimes fall on deaf ears. But this only leads you further down the spiral, as you enact even more vicious studies that threaten to unravel your grasp of sanity.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you fail to perform Hypnosis, both you and the patient suffer from Stress."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"nCENNgYKNL3hTVRS","name":"Warp Dissonance","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The mind reels at the complexities of the Ætheric Winds and how they pass into the Material Realm. The mortal soul is not properly equipped to deal with these confounding majesties and can easily overwhelm even its most learned of practitioners. It takes solemnity and inner grace to properly balance oneself against the buffeting Winds of the Æther, one that must be unburdened by woe.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you are suffering from 6 or more Corruption, you cannot Channel Power."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"pJwERZsv8Is9ijRD","name":"Psychotic Break","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"One must have a callous indifference towards the sanctity of life to move from being a tourney archer to a hunter of men. Targeteers who are consumed by the act of killing are utterly corrupted, while others who maintain proper decorum will remain untainted by their grisly work.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you take an innocent life unprovoked, you automatically gain 1 permanent Chaos Rank."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"phizICpXwZJWlOHL","name":"Black Marketeer","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Every time some stolen good passes from your hands to another, you cannot shake the feeling that somebody is watching you.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever attempting to buy, sell or trade stolen goods, you cannot use Fortune Points to modify your Skill Test results."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"pjDPQtEHlxLSabWe","name":"Sea Legs","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/at-sea.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You live for the sea and the rising of the tide. But when you stand on land, the swell of the sea fills your head with dizziness.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When not borne upon water or a boat, reduce your Initiative by your Chaos Ranks (to a minimum of 1)."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"pyPi0Qo3V5CmE5uZ","name":"The End is Nigh","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Unfortunately, the process of ritual scarification has led its votaries toward the brink of madness.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can never be restored to Unharmed on your Damage Condition Track, only to Lightly Wounded."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"q7lIGDIlm27R5Qp3","name":"Painkiller","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/skull-with-syringe.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You escape the stresses of your daily life – and the horrors of what’s out there – by self-medicating.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Work with your GM to select a single Addiction your Character begins play with."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"qHnoJ4r8wLc9ZCDr","name":"Ambition Denied","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Petty squabbling and infighting reigns among the forces of Corruption. The rank and file rarely engage openly in such activities, crushed and cowed as they are by their officers, but between its lieutenants it can run rampant, the machinations of others apparent to you connive, deceive and maneuver your way through the ranks. When your plans and connivances succeed, you are exultant, but when they go awry, you fall into a fit of self-loathing and despair.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You immediately gain a Disorder. In addition, for every enemy that is Slain! by your allies you did not render the killing blow to, you gain 3 Corruption."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"qSJi8XquSugfuHSy","name":"The Steward’s Commandments","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/wax-tablet.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Steward makes specific demands from His priesthood. They must always obey their superiors, always honor surrender, and never kill their prisoners unless in self-defense. Unfortunately, this often puts them at odds with the followers of the Winter King, who embrace warmongering as a means to an end.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you would normally invoke a Chaos Manifestation, you instead provoke Punishments of the Steward. In addition, you are bound by the commandments of your god. You must seek atonement if you violate these commandments."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"qTRuHM080QpDvMgc","name":"Celebrity Status","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/laurel-crown.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Everywhere you go, your renown precedes you. It makes it difficult to find a quiet spot at the local watering hole and especially hard to get any work done when your admirers are gathered in throngs outside the doorstep!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When in places where you may be recognized by your real name or by your works, you suffer from Stress."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"qcXF72cbUSSBao4k","name":"Ne'er Do Well","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are feckless, irresponsible and prone to idleness. It doesn’t mean that you are completely useless, however, you are unreliable when the chips are down.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You cannot Assist others’ Skill Tests."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"rEwiuhbdlhQZPaFX","name":"Do You Know Who I Am?","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Burgomasters are often dogmatic in their worldview and impart these same values over the people they rule over.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately change your Order Alignment to Dignity and your Chaos Alignment to Vehemence."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"rd2e2vdT7U1cWOa1","name":"The Nightfather’s Commandments","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/wax-tablet.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Nightfather makes specific demands from His priesthood. This includes participation in gambling, theft and graft. The use of violence is highly discouraged; even muggings and petty crimes where others are brought to harm is looked down upon. Informing upon criminal activities of others, however, is the most egregious of sins in the eyes of the Nightfather.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you would normally invoke a Chaos Manifestation, you instead provoke Punishments of the Nightfather. In addition, you are bound by the commandments of your god. You must seek atonement if you violate these commandments"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"s15Vp05YdK0dXlkV","name":"Phlegmatic Temperament","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/breaking-chain.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"In a nutshell, you have a tendency to withdraw from the world when things get tough. And, when subjected to horrific situations, you become indecisive and meek.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you are suffering from Stress, Fear or Terror, your Fury Dice do not explode (as covered in Chapter 2: How To Play). This lasts until you get a good night's rest."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"sbky0zrQ9jIW4qOm","name":"White Temperament","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Possessed by an unyielding quest for enlightenment – quite literally – as their bodies become a vessel for Luminescence. This unification of spirit, mind and body attunes them to the Ætheric Winds of the Material Realm. When the sun sets, however, the light is sapped from them, and they are made victim to the encroaching darkness.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"At nighttime, you cannot cast Magick without Channeling Power."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"sj2TdgXtDljxUqXN","name":"Black Cataract","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Your eye has grown over with glaucoma or suffered major trauma in a fight or accident. As a result, you have difficulty making out distances and depth. It’s not to say that you cannot see, but you face extreme hardship, unable to discern between friend or foe at times.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you miss with Attack Actions using a ranged weapon, you must re-roll the result with the same Difficulty Rating. If it is a success, you strike a random ally who is Engaged with your target."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"uklFdmv3QC7mX7Sh","name":"The Winter King’s Commandments","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/wax-tablet.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Winter King makes specific demands from His priesthood. They will not lie, cheat or lay in wait to ambush their enemies. Wolf-skins are sacred and must be worn at all times – even when in bed. Fires must be kept alight while resting, lest Abyssal spirits invade their dreams. Males will not shave their beards until defeated in combat, whereas women will wear their hair braided until they suffer the same fate. Bravery and self-reliance are the watchwords of the White Wolves.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you would normally invoke a Chaos Manifestation, you instead provoke Punishments of the Winter King. In addition, you are bound by the commandments of your god. You must seek atonement if you violate these commandments."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"v2PvssHRQo2MuuBt","name":"A Grim Career","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/convince.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The life of an executioner means they are shamed and feared by the smallfolk, despite their grisly (yet lawful) task.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Permanently lower your Fellowship by 9%."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"xFOby2mzPD7EsR8L","name":"Veteran's Eye","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You have lost an eye. It may have been from a childhood prank gone wrong, an abnormality from birth or the ‘devil’ made you gouge it out. Regardless, you may have a glass bead where it once was, wear an eye patch over the empty socket or simply let its hollowed-out recess go uncovered.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Reduce the Distance for all ranged weapons you use by -3 (to a minimum of 1)."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"xUJVQVnYrhaPCutx","name":"The Customer is Always Right","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Shopkeepers adhere to the time-honored rule that the customer is always right. This has been a throne in the side of every Shopkeeper for generations, but ensures that their dealings are seen as upright.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you fail at an attempt to use Bargain or Rumor, you cannot use Fortune Points to change your results."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"xzDudTKFXITqfQ2X","name":"The Demiurge’s Commandments","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/wax-tablet.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Demiurge makes specific demands from Its priesthood. This includes sacrificial offerings, seclusion during the winter solstice for extended prayer and jubilant exhortation during the spring solstice.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you would normally invoke a Chaos Manifestation, you instead provoke Punishments of the Demiurge. In addition, you are bound by the commandments of your god. You must seek atonement if you violate these commandments."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ylQwBhYJRPXw7c4N","name":"Book of Grudges","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Through the annals of time, Oathkeeper’s kinfolk have been felled by many rival tribes. Those who bring you to the end of their blade will remain your enemy forever, both kith and kin.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"After you have been Injured or Slain! by a creature and survived (providing it is classified as a Humanoid, Mutant or of a player Ancestries), their kind then becomes your grudge-born enemy. When your grudge-born enemy attacks, they always add a 1D6 Fury Die to melee weapon Damage against you. In addition, they are immune to the Intimidate Skill – along with Stress, Fear and Terror – used by you. Note that there is no upper limit to the number of chosen grudge-borne enemies types an Oathkeeper can have."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"zdZuoVIvCnxgsUny","name":"Public Enemy","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/spiked-halo.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Your face and name are well-known. Very likely, there’s a reeve, bounty hunter or worse on your tail. As such, you are forced to live a life in the shadows, using trusted confidantes to carry out your tasks in public.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When in places where you may be recognized, you cannot use Fortune Points unless you make means to hide your true identity. The GM will likely ask you to make a Secret Test for Disguise when in public, only revealing the results at the most inopportune of times."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"zuB1x7g2AZzswAWd","name":"Overworked","type":"drawback","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/sleepy.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The long hours can lead to stress, anxiety and depression... making you an easy target for the influence of Corruption.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you suffer\n  Peril due to Stress, Fear\n  or Terror, move one additional step down the Peril Condition Track negatively while suffering 1 additional Corruption."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{}}
